This sounds (to me) more compatible with the topic-only version of
the grammar than it is with one that implements the different gapping
possibilities.  Is that what you mean?  On the other hand, it also
assumes that we're basically not looking at any long-distance dependencies.
If the argument is a gapped one (rather than just topic-linked), it
belongs with the highest verb.  Is that defensible (even statistically)?
Or am I missing something?

