I think it might be a little different. Presumably, if there are
intransitive verbs functioning as relative clauses that actually
resist the topic-like relative clause construction, then there are
also transitive verbs that do so.  Whether or not they end up leading
to ambiguous relative clauses wouldn't depend on whether there is
also pro-drop of some argument in addition to the gapped argument.


