My untested assumption is that the distribution of topics and the
distribution of relative clauses is different enough that an
interpreter (back-end system) will want different parameters in
resolving them.  For example I am pretty sure that o-kaku is quite
rare as a topic (much less than 7%), although I can't find any data at
hand.

